						               													<description>Cards have a number (1-7) at the top, and a hole at the bottom. Each player starts each round with 7 cards. The starting player plays a card face up to the discard pile. In turn order, players discard a card directly on top of the discard pile, either playing hole-on-hole or hole-on-number. The sum of visible numbers must be equal to or greater than the previous sum, but no higher than 7.&amp;#10;- If you cannot play, take a penalty card -- turn over.&amp;#10;- If you discard a card and the sum is not 7, draw a card -- play passes to next clockwise player.&amp;#10;- If the sum is 7, set aside that discard pile and start a new one by playing another card -- your turn is over (do not draw a card).&amp;#10;If a new draw pile is needed, shuffle all cards already set aside.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When a player runs out of cards (plays their last card creating a sum of 7), they take 1 VP chip + 1 chip per player remaining. Play continues until only 1 player is left with cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;With 2-4 players, the game ends after 7 rounds; with 5-7 players, play till the VP chips have all been handed out. The player with the most VP wins!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
